1
00:00:33,054 --> 00:00:36,057
PRO BONO

2
00:00:37,684 --> 00:00:42,313
The plaintiff Kaya had already given birth
in her country before she got married.

3
00:00:43,565 --> 00:00:46,860
What? What on earth is he talking about?

4
00:00:47,569 --> 00:00:48,862
It's not true, is it?

5
00:00:48,945 --> 00:00:51,072
The plaintiff hid the fact
that she had given birth

6
00:00:51,155 --> 00:00:52,323
and deceived the defendant

7
00:00:52,991 --> 00:00:54,158
for a fraudulent marriage.

8
00:00:54,784 --> 00:00:55,743
Why didn't you tell us?

9
00:00:55,827 --> 00:00:58,872
You gave birth before marriage?
Is that really true, Kaya?

10
00:00:58,955 --> 00:01:01,416
We're in a totally different
situation now.

11
00:01:02,292 --> 00:01:04,669
An annulment of marriage
is different from a divorce.

12
00:01:04,752 --> 00:01:06,754
It nullifies the marriage itself,

13
00:01:06,838 --> 00:01:09,549
so it'll be
as if you were never married at all.

14
00:01:09,632 --> 00:01:12,844
The marriage visa you used to come here
will be canceled.

15
00:01:12,927 --> 00:01:15,847
You'll be kicked out
from this country, Kaya!

16
00:01:16,431 --> 00:01:17,265
What?

17
00:01:18,391 --> 00:01:23,313
PRO BONO

18
00:01:24,856 --> 00:01:26,149
It's one problem after another.

19
00:01:26,232 --> 00:01:29,193
Just as we uncovered the truth,
a marriage annulment?

20
00:01:29,277 --> 00:01:32,530
They want a marriage annulment
after sexually abusing her?

21
00:01:33,197 --> 00:01:35,658
This is something
you can't fix with a legal approach.

22
00:01:35,742 --> 00:01:37,827
-We need to use our fists!
-Hey!

23
00:01:37,911 --> 00:01:39,037
Calm down.

24
00:01:39,537 --> 00:01:40,788
No need to get worked up.

25
00:01:41,414 --> 00:01:43,833
What we do
is someone else's problem in the end.

26
00:01:43,917 --> 00:01:46,461
What? How could you say
something like that?

27
00:01:47,420 --> 00:01:48,296
With my mouth.

28
00:01:51,883 --> 00:01:53,635
-"With my mouth!"
-Ms. Park!

29
00:01:53,718 --> 00:01:54,844
Yes?

30
00:01:56,012 --> 00:01:58,765
You all remember you have
medical checkups this week, right?

31
00:01:59,599 --> 00:02:01,768
That also includes our new hire, Mr. Kang.

32
00:02:01,851 --> 00:02:04,938
Don't miss it this time. Where's Mr. Jang?

33
00:02:05,021 --> 00:02:06,231
I can take it.

34
00:02:06,314 --> 00:02:08,024
Right now, we don't have time to--

35
00:02:08,107 --> 00:02:09,984
It's company policy for all employees.

36
00:02:10,068 --> 00:02:11,569
There's an endoscopy as well,

37
00:02:11,653 --> 00:02:14,113
so please start fasting
from the night before.

38
00:02:15,240 --> 00:02:17,617
Geez. How could the least busy team
not have time?

39
00:02:17,700 --> 00:02:19,869
Hold on. What did you just say?

40
00:02:19,953 --> 00:02:21,329
Have a nice day.

41
00:02:21,996 --> 00:02:24,999
Don't get heated.
If they want us to do it, we'll do it.

42
00:02:25,083 --> 00:02:28,044
Do you know you're making me
even more heated?

43
00:02:30,004 --> 00:02:31,506
Then, cool down.

44
00:02:33,675 --> 00:02:35,385
BLOOD PRESSURE RANGES

45
00:02:50,024 --> 00:02:51,734
I didn't put it in yet.

46
00:02:52,568 --> 00:02:54,195
Breathe in.

47
00:02:54,904 --> 00:02:55,863
And hold.

48
00:02:58,908 --> 00:03:00,243
Six, two, eight, three, five.

49
00:03:00,326 --> 00:03:02,286
-And this?
-8, 3, 5, 2, 9.

50
00:03:02,370 --> 00:03:04,080
-And now?
-5, 9, 6, 4, 2.

51
00:03:04,163 --> 00:03:05,164
-And?
-2, 9, 5, 7, 4.

52
00:03:05,248 --> 00:03:06,666
-Now?
-3, 8, 2, 3, 7.

53
00:03:08,084 --> 00:03:10,795
Four, three…

54
00:03:13,006 --> 00:03:13,923
See?

55
00:03:15,258 --> 00:03:16,759
My body doesn't respond

56
00:03:17,343 --> 00:03:21,472
to anesthesia…

57
00:03:21,556 --> 00:03:22,974
What doesn't respond?

58
00:03:27,145 --> 00:03:28,104
Ms. Park.

59
00:03:30,064 --> 00:03:31,566
You're not getting the endoscopy?

60
00:03:35,445 --> 00:03:39,032
We've already returned to work
after finishing our checkups.

61
00:03:39,657 --> 00:03:42,744
You're the only one who's late
after making a big fuss.

62
00:03:46,372 --> 00:03:49,500
Gosh, it was so hilarious though.
It's a shame only I saw it.

63
00:03:49,584 --> 00:03:52,795
What are you talking about?
Did I say something?

64
00:03:52,879 --> 00:03:54,964
Forget it.
Go get changed and come out.

65
00:03:55,631 --> 00:03:56,466
Come on out.

66
00:03:57,842 --> 00:03:58,676
What?

67
00:04:00,178 --> 00:04:01,054
What on earth?

68
00:04:07,310 --> 00:04:09,020
SUWON FAMILY COURT
SINGLE-JUDGE DIVISION

69
00:04:09,103 --> 00:04:10,855
"Marriage is a sacred promise."

70
00:04:10,938 --> 00:04:13,649
"Just as a castle built on sand
doesn't last,

71
00:04:14,317 --> 00:04:18,821
a marriage built on lies
cannot be continued."

72
00:04:19,447 --> 00:04:21,324
"Judge Gu Ji-won."

73
00:04:21,407 --> 00:04:23,117
I admire you, Your Honor.

74
00:04:23,201 --> 00:04:27,330
While working
as a family court judge for ten years,

75
00:04:27,413 --> 00:04:29,665
you've emphasized
the importance of being faithful

76
00:04:29,749 --> 00:04:31,084
in a marital relationship.

77
00:04:31,167 --> 00:04:34,212
Marital history, parental status,
and criminal record.

78
00:04:34,295 --> 00:04:35,630
Whatever it may be,

79
00:04:36,172 --> 00:04:38,174
when someone married through deception,

80
00:04:38,257 --> 00:04:41,010
you didn't hesitate
to annul their marriage.

81
00:04:41,094 --> 00:04:42,887
I've only ruled according to the law.

82
00:04:42,970 --> 00:04:44,097
Yes, Your Honor.

83
00:04:44,680 --> 00:04:49,769
For this case, please render justice
according to the law as well.

84
00:04:49,852 --> 00:04:52,563
Article 816, Paragraph 3 of the Civil Act.

85
00:04:52,647 --> 00:04:54,649
"When the declaration
of intention to marry

86
00:04:54,732 --> 00:04:56,567
has been made
through fraud or under duress…"

87
00:04:56,651 --> 00:04:59,570
If hiding childbirth history
doesn't fall under this,

88
00:04:59,654 --> 00:05:02,657
I don't know what would.

89
00:05:03,324 --> 00:05:06,702
Is the plaintiff going to accept
the physical examination

90
00:05:06,786 --> 00:05:08,454
to reveal her childbirth history?

91
00:05:11,749 --> 00:05:13,334
I'm sorry, Your Honor.

92
00:05:13,418 --> 00:05:16,629
The physical examination
won't be necessary.

93
00:05:17,338 --> 00:05:18,589
That means…

94
00:05:18,673 --> 00:05:21,300
We admit the fact
that the plaintiff gave birth…

95
00:05:23,136 --> 00:05:24,137
before this marriage.

96
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:27,849
That damn bitch!

97
00:05:27,932 --> 00:05:29,267
Is that true, Ms. Kaya?

98
00:05:29,350 --> 00:05:30,393
Kaya.

99
00:05:40,945 --> 00:05:42,071
Yes, Your Honor.

100
00:05:45,867 --> 00:05:49,203
At first, you filed a lawsuit,
claiming your husband strangled you.

101
00:05:49,287 --> 00:05:52,915
Now, are you saying
you had a child before your marriage?

102
00:05:52,999 --> 00:05:56,377
I don't know which part
of your story is true anymore.

103
00:05:56,919 --> 00:05:58,296
My apologies, Your Honor.

104
00:05:58,880 --> 00:06:01,716
We will make sure
to reveal the whole truth.

105
00:06:02,508 --> 00:06:05,595
Please allow us to examine
the plaintiff one more time.

106
00:06:08,181 --> 00:06:09,182
WITNESS

107
00:06:09,265 --> 00:06:10,683
Thank you, Your Honor.

108
00:06:12,101 --> 00:06:13,603
Have you given birth to a child

109
00:06:13,686 --> 00:06:16,022
before you got married?

110
00:06:23,613 --> 00:06:24,447
Yes.

111
00:06:26,240 --> 00:06:27,992
How old were you then?

112
00:06:32,622 --> 00:06:34,415
I was 14 years old.

113
00:06:37,251 --> 00:06:39,045
How old was the child's father?

114
00:06:40,796 --> 00:06:43,132
He was 32.

115
00:06:43,216 --> 00:06:44,550
Did you know him?

116
00:06:45,801 --> 00:06:48,512
I'd never seen him before.

117
00:06:51,349 --> 00:06:54,101
I know it's hard, but please tell us.

118
00:06:55,353 --> 00:06:56,687
What exactly happened?

119
00:07:03,736 --> 00:07:04,654
When I…

120
00:07:07,114 --> 00:07:09,408
When I was 13,

121
00:07:11,410 --> 00:07:15,915
I was picking firewood in the mountains.

122
00:07:25,216 --> 00:07:27,134
He kidnapped me.

123
00:07:30,763 --> 00:07:31,597
And…

124
00:07:32,181 --> 00:07:33,516
No!

125
00:07:34,100 --> 00:07:35,142
No!

126
00:07:36,060 --> 00:07:37,478
It's a lie!

127
00:07:37,562 --> 00:07:39,272
Son! Dong-min!

128
00:07:39,355 --> 00:07:43,442
I'm sorry, Your Honor,
but may we have a short recess?

129
00:07:48,364 --> 00:07:49,615
COURT 301, TODAY'S TRIALS

130
00:07:53,995 --> 00:07:54,912
It's hard, isn't it?

131
00:07:56,330 --> 00:07:57,373
Ms. Park.

132
00:08:00,293 --> 00:08:02,044
This is just the beginning.

133
00:08:03,546 --> 00:08:07,091
You have to remember every detail
of that terrible incident

134
00:08:07,675 --> 00:08:10,970
and say them as is.

135
00:08:12,388 --> 00:08:15,600
A trial can be really cruel.

136
00:08:19,270 --> 00:08:22,815
Kaya. You can do it, right?

137
00:08:27,695 --> 00:08:28,529
COURT IN SESSION

138
00:08:28,613 --> 00:08:30,364
-Well done.
-Thank you.

139
00:08:33,701 --> 00:08:34,869
Your Honor.

140
00:08:34,952 --> 00:08:36,787
As you have just heard,

141
00:08:36,871 --> 00:08:41,375
she was only 13 when she was abducted
by a man in a neighboring village.

142
00:08:41,459 --> 00:08:45,212
She was confined in his house
and sexually assaulted for a week.

143
00:08:55,222 --> 00:08:59,101
She had an unwanted pregnancy
as a result of that sexual assault.

144
00:08:59,185 --> 00:09:03,272
If necessary, we'll present the neighbors
from her village as witnesses.

145
00:09:03,356 --> 00:09:04,231
I'm sorry, but…

146
00:09:04,315 --> 00:09:08,444
First off, thank you for the examination.
You prepared very well.

147
00:09:08,944 --> 00:09:12,073
But was this information even necessary?

148
00:09:12,865 --> 00:09:16,911
Did the defendant's counsel
not hear a word of the examination?

149
00:09:17,453 --> 00:09:19,288
When she was 13, she was locked--

150
00:09:19,372 --> 00:09:22,083
And so what does that
have to do with this case?

151
00:09:29,048 --> 00:09:33,094
I'm not a heartless, merciless person.

152
00:09:33,844 --> 00:09:37,932
It must have been terrible to go through
such a thing at a young age.

153
00:09:38,015 --> 00:09:42,269
Regardless of the reason she gave birth,

154
00:09:42,353 --> 00:09:46,273
I am not here to hold her responsible
for the childbirth itself.

155
00:09:46,357 --> 00:09:52,321
I am asking her why she did not tell
her spouse-to-be such an important fact

156
00:09:52,405 --> 00:09:55,116
before getting married.

157
00:09:55,199 --> 00:09:56,158
Am I wrong?

158
00:09:56,242 --> 00:09:58,452
How is this any different
from a fraudulent car dealer

159
00:09:58,536 --> 00:10:01,831
who sells a car
by highlighting only its positive aspects

160
00:10:01,914 --> 00:10:03,749
while concealing its negative ones?

161
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:06,836
The defendant, as you just saw…

162
00:10:07,420 --> 00:10:10,923
He's not someone who can hide anything.

163
00:10:11,006 --> 00:10:12,007
But the plaintiff,

164
00:10:12,091 --> 00:10:16,887
who is so smart she studied Korean
on her own to speak it fluently,

165
00:10:16,971 --> 00:10:18,973
failed to say a single word to Mr. Cho

166
00:10:19,056 --> 00:10:22,309
about this significant matter
before getting married.

167
00:10:22,393 --> 00:10:25,896
Is this really being faithful
to one's future spouse?

168
00:10:27,732 --> 00:10:30,651
-Then, let me ask the defendant's counsel.
-Yes.

169
00:10:30,735 --> 00:10:33,320
Before you got married,
have you told your wife

170
00:10:33,404 --> 00:10:37,074
everything about getting bitten by a dog
when you were young?

171
00:10:37,158 --> 00:10:39,785
What kind of pointless question is this?

172
00:10:39,869 --> 00:10:41,245
-How is this any different?
-What?

173
00:10:41,328 --> 00:10:44,331
The plaintiff was basically bitten
by a mad dog.

174
00:10:44,415 --> 00:10:48,377
She was subjected to an assault
completely against her will.

175
00:10:49,128 --> 00:10:51,380
Fundamentally, what's so different?

176
00:10:51,464 --> 00:10:54,091
-But still, this is--
-I see.

177
00:10:54,175 --> 00:10:55,926
It's different
because it's sexual assault?

178
00:10:56,427 --> 00:10:58,387
Because it involves sex?

179
00:10:58,471 --> 00:11:00,347
Then, let me ask you again.

180
00:11:01,015 --> 00:11:02,892
Before getting married,
did you tell your wife

181
00:11:02,975 --> 00:11:04,935
about all of your sexual partners

182
00:11:05,019 --> 00:11:07,396
and about when, where,
and every detail of--

183
00:11:07,480 --> 00:11:09,273
What on earth are you doing right now?

184
00:11:09,857 --> 00:11:12,526
Plaintiff's counsel,
I see the point you want to make.

185
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:14,487
But please make your argument
more serious.

186
00:11:15,571 --> 00:11:17,573
Did I go overboard?

187
00:11:18,240 --> 00:11:20,409
My apologies if I did, Your Honor.

188
00:11:20,493 --> 00:11:25,331
I am just asking whether the argument
that the defense claims is so obvious

189
00:11:25,414 --> 00:11:27,416
is truly obvious.

190
00:11:27,500 --> 00:11:30,586
Still, the history of childbirth
is another story.

191
00:11:30,669 --> 00:11:32,922
"Your wife-to-be has a child."

192
00:11:33,923 --> 00:11:35,424
What's more crucial than that?

193
00:11:35,508 --> 00:11:39,094
The assailant's parents
took the baby right after it was born.

194
00:11:39,178 --> 00:11:42,598
She has never met
or seen the baby since then.

195
00:11:42,681 --> 00:11:45,017
But we can't predict the future, can we?

196
00:11:45,100 --> 00:11:48,646
We also do not know
how giving birth at such a young age

197
00:11:48,729 --> 00:11:51,732
will affect
future pregnancies or childbirth.

198
00:11:51,815 --> 00:11:53,567
History of childbirth

199
00:11:53,651 --> 00:11:58,614
is one of the most important facts
that must be disclosed before marriage.

200
00:11:58,697 --> 00:12:00,032
Isn't that common sense?

201
00:12:00,699 --> 00:12:03,994
The plaintiff's counsel is desperately
using all sorts of misleading arguments

202
00:12:04,078 --> 00:12:07,957
to divert our attention
from this common sense,

203
00:12:08,040 --> 00:12:08,874
Your Honor.

204
00:12:13,128 --> 00:12:17,341
He's a former SPO prosecutor all right.
How do we defend against this?

205
00:12:20,177 --> 00:12:22,930
I admit it. That is common sense.

206
00:12:24,974 --> 00:12:25,975
It's important.

207
00:12:26,058 --> 00:12:28,769
The law should be based on common sense.

208
00:12:29,478 --> 00:12:31,855
However, sometimes…

209
00:12:31,939 --> 00:12:33,649
Once in a while,

210
00:12:34,358 --> 00:12:36,986
common sense can miss some things.

211
00:12:37,695 --> 00:12:42,283
Most people don't experience
what Kaya went through.

212
00:12:42,366 --> 00:12:46,412
At the young age of 13, she was kidnapped,
confined, and sexually assaulted.

213
00:12:46,495 --> 00:12:48,497
Common sense can easily fail to grasp

214
00:12:49,373 --> 00:12:52,543
the pain and fear of such a person.

215
00:12:53,252 --> 00:12:55,754
To resolve this discrepancy,

216
00:12:56,380 --> 00:12:59,008
the Constitution protects
fundamental human rights.

217
00:12:59,091 --> 00:13:00,593
Article 17 of the Constitution.

218
00:13:00,676 --> 00:13:01,802
"No citizen shall have

219
00:13:02,428 --> 00:13:05,764
their right to privacy and freedom
of private life infringed upon."

220
00:13:05,848 --> 00:13:08,684
There are some things in this world

221
00:13:08,767 --> 00:13:12,104
that are just too cruel
to demand disclosure.

222
00:13:12,187 --> 00:13:15,357
Yes, it is true
that having a history of pregnancy

223
00:13:15,441 --> 00:13:17,026
is an important fact

224
00:13:17,109 --> 00:13:19,069
that should be notified
to a future spouse.

225
00:13:19,153 --> 00:13:20,279
It's common sense.

226
00:13:20,362 --> 00:13:22,281
However, when it comes

227
00:13:22,364 --> 00:13:25,701
to basic human rights
protected by the Constitution,

228
00:13:25,784 --> 00:13:29,079
shouldn't common sense
at least allow an exception?

229
00:13:30,205 --> 00:13:32,499
Compelling a victim of child sexual abuse

230
00:13:32,583 --> 00:13:35,878
to disclose what happened to her…

231
00:13:35,961 --> 00:13:38,047
How could… Hey, how could you do that?

232
00:13:40,716 --> 00:13:41,759
Your Honor.

233
00:13:42,801 --> 00:13:45,512
Please look
at the big picture of this case.

234
00:13:46,013 --> 00:13:49,099
This is the case
of a child sexual abuse victim

235
00:13:49,183 --> 00:13:51,769
requesting to end a marriage
that cannot continue

236
00:13:51,852 --> 00:13:56,106
after being sexually abused again
by her father-in-law.

237
00:13:56,774 --> 00:13:59,234
But the assailant, her in-laws…

238
00:14:00,152 --> 00:14:02,279
Her in-laws,
who haven't apologized at all,

239
00:14:02,363 --> 00:14:06,033
are actually trying to use
the child sexual abuse she went through

240
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:10,120
as a reason to deny
and annul this marriage.

241
00:14:11,622 --> 00:14:13,165
According to my common sense,

242
00:14:13,248 --> 00:14:15,959
this is the culprit
pretending to be the victim…

243
00:14:17,795 --> 00:14:19,421
and it's despicable retaliation.

244
00:14:22,216 --> 00:14:23,175
Your Honor.

245
00:14:23,884 --> 00:14:27,179
Between my common sense
and the defense's,

246
00:14:27,262 --> 00:14:30,683
I kindly ask you to make a wise judgment
as to which one is correct.

247
00:14:44,905 --> 00:14:48,492
Your Honor,
I would also like to add a few words.

248
00:14:48,575 --> 00:14:49,952
I am not saying

249
00:14:51,662 --> 00:14:55,165
that the plaintiff should have told
any random person on the street

250
00:14:55,249 --> 00:14:57,334
about what she had gone through.

251
00:14:58,627 --> 00:15:01,088
We are arguing
she should have told

252
00:15:01,672 --> 00:15:04,925
the person she would spend
the rest of her life with,

253
00:15:05,009 --> 00:15:06,510
her spouse-to-be.

254
00:15:06,593 --> 00:15:10,305
But she hid the fact
instead of telling him. Why?

255
00:15:10,389 --> 00:15:11,724
She knew perfectly well

256
00:15:11,807 --> 00:15:15,144
that he wouldn't marry her
once she told the truth.

257
00:15:15,227 --> 00:15:19,565
If that's not a fraudulent marriage,
then what is, Your Honor?

258
00:15:19,648 --> 00:15:22,526
Despite the fancy arguments made
by the plaintiff's counsel,

259
00:15:22,609 --> 00:15:25,571
the nature of the case has not changed.

260
00:15:26,572 --> 00:15:27,698
Marriage is a contract.

261
00:15:27,781 --> 00:15:31,160
And a fraudulent contract can be annulled.

262
00:15:31,785 --> 00:15:35,748
Please rule on the principles, Your Honor.

263
00:15:45,883 --> 00:15:49,428
-You did a great job, Mr. Kang.
-You too, Ms. Park.

264
00:15:51,513 --> 00:15:53,265
Thank you, both.

265
00:15:55,059 --> 00:15:56,268
Kaya.

266
00:15:56,351 --> 00:16:00,147
This judge is known for being stubborn
and adhering to principles.

267
00:16:01,398 --> 00:16:02,816
She has previously ruled

268
00:16:02,900 --> 00:16:05,569
in favor of annulment before
due to childbirth history.

269
00:16:05,652 --> 00:16:09,782
She won't go against
her past rulings that easily.

270
00:16:10,491 --> 00:16:11,825
Even so, it's fine.

271
00:16:13,994 --> 00:16:14,828
What?

272
00:16:14,912 --> 00:16:18,749
For the first time in my life,
someone stood up for me.

273
00:16:19,500 --> 00:16:23,796
And it was in this faraway land
where I'm a foreigner.

274
00:16:26,048 --> 00:16:28,634
Thank you so much.

275
00:16:41,563 --> 00:16:43,107
Congratulations, Mr. Kang.

276
00:16:43,732 --> 00:16:46,276
-What?
-I think you've taken your first step

277
00:16:46,360 --> 00:16:48,612
as a public interest attorney.

278
00:16:49,279 --> 00:16:51,115
What do you mean by that?

279
00:16:51,782 --> 00:16:54,409
You went into a fight,
knowing that you'll lose.

280
00:16:55,619 --> 00:16:56,954
That's a pro bono attorney.

281
00:16:59,706 --> 00:17:01,083
That is certainly not my thing.

282
00:17:05,170 --> 00:17:06,964
My car is this way.

283
00:17:07,589 --> 00:17:08,549
I know.

284
00:17:16,598 --> 00:17:19,518
Civil case number 2025-674221.

285
00:17:20,144 --> 00:17:22,646
Civil case number 2025-674519.

286
00:17:23,397 --> 00:17:25,399
The Court will deliver the verdict.

287
00:17:25,482 --> 00:17:29,153
Article 816, Paragraph 3
of the Civil Act states

288
00:17:29,862 --> 00:17:33,365
when the declaration of intention to marry

289
00:17:33,448 --> 00:17:35,784
has been made
through fraud or under duress

290
00:17:36,410 --> 00:17:40,914
a spouse can request
to annul the marriage.

291
00:17:40,998 --> 00:17:44,293
Before two people enter
the serious promise called marriage,

292
00:17:44,376 --> 00:17:46,962
they should not withhold
any lies from each other.

293
00:17:47,045 --> 00:17:50,924
Not to mention that having given birth
before the marriage

294
00:17:51,008 --> 00:17:55,512
is an important fact that can affect
the marriage in a tremendous way.

295
00:17:55,596 --> 00:17:56,972
So of course,

296
00:17:57,055 --> 00:18:00,309
a soon-to-be wife is obligated
to notify her potential husband.

297
00:18:01,351 --> 00:18:03,061
However…

298
00:18:04,229 --> 00:18:05,105
However,

299
00:18:06,690 --> 00:18:10,861
there are times
when the law must allow exceptions.

300
00:18:11,612 --> 00:18:14,656
It is true that the plaintiff
gave birth to a child,

301
00:18:14,740 --> 00:18:17,075
but it was against her own will,

302
00:18:17,159 --> 00:18:20,579
and she was the victim
of child sexual abuse.

303
00:18:21,747 --> 00:18:25,167
And the relationship with the baby
was severed a long time ago.

304
00:18:25,709 --> 00:18:28,503
It cannot be denied
that it is excessively cruel

305
00:18:28,587 --> 00:18:31,798
to compel the victim of a crime

306
00:18:31,882 --> 00:18:34,635
to bear the duty of disclosing
what they went through.

307
00:18:35,761 --> 00:18:40,182
Therefore, the plaintiff's failure
to disclose her childbirth history

308
00:18:40,265 --> 00:18:43,393
does not warrant condemnation

309
00:18:43,477 --> 00:18:46,355
in light of her duty of good faith.

310
00:18:46,438 --> 00:18:48,190
The Court renders the following judgment.

311
00:18:48,857 --> 00:18:49,691
The Court orders…

312
00:18:51,777 --> 00:18:55,530
the plaintiff and the defendant
to divorce as a result of this case.

313
00:18:58,408 --> 00:19:01,328
The defendant's counterclaim is dismissed.

314
00:19:06,083 --> 00:19:07,793
You have won, Plaintiff.

315
00:19:10,462 --> 00:19:12,172
This is absurd!

316
00:19:12,256 --> 00:19:13,882
This is a scam!

317
00:19:14,508 --> 00:19:16,426
-Ridiculous! You bitch!
-Thank you, Your Honor.

318
00:19:17,177 --> 00:19:19,346
Let go of me! Mr. Woo!

319
00:19:19,429 --> 00:19:20,973
We won!

320
00:19:21,056 --> 00:19:23,976
Do I get to live in Korea?

321
00:19:24,059 --> 00:19:25,560
-Really?
-Yes!

322
00:19:29,231 --> 00:19:31,191
Thank you, Ms. Park!

323
00:19:31,275 --> 00:19:32,442
COURT 301, TODAY'S TRIALS

324
00:19:35,779 --> 00:19:36,613
Geez.

325
00:19:37,239 --> 00:19:40,450
You upset the order of the court
with cheap sentimentality.

326
00:19:40,534 --> 00:19:44,329
-Stop it. You're dropping our standard.
-What? I dropped something?

327
00:19:52,671 --> 00:19:54,298
Shut it.

328
00:19:55,507 --> 00:19:56,425
See you soon.

329
00:19:57,676 --> 00:20:01,179
Sure, sure.

330
00:20:02,180 --> 00:20:05,142
-Will they appeal?
-Well, it's up to them.

331
00:20:05,976 --> 00:20:07,602
-Anyway, Ms. Park.
-Yes?

332
00:20:07,686 --> 00:20:10,188
I'll treat you to a meal since we won.

333
00:20:10,272 --> 00:20:12,065
-Now?
-Aren't you hungry?

334
00:20:16,278 --> 00:20:17,112
What's he up to?

335
00:20:18,071 --> 00:20:20,741
Gosh. This burger is so good.

336
00:20:21,950 --> 00:20:23,702
And the view's great too.

337
00:20:26,538 --> 00:20:27,706
What's gotten into you today?

338
00:20:29,750 --> 00:20:32,586
Now that the trial is over,
we need to talk.

339
00:20:33,128 --> 00:20:34,504
Attorney Park Gi-ppeum.

340
00:20:34,588 --> 00:20:35,922
She's an interesting one.

341
00:20:36,840 --> 00:20:38,175
Ms. Park? Why?

342
00:20:38,258 --> 00:20:39,384
She threatened me

343
00:20:40,552 --> 00:20:41,803
with your video.

344
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:45,015
I heard you saw the video.

345
00:20:48,643 --> 00:20:49,478
Yes.

346
00:20:53,607 --> 00:20:54,441
Who sent it?

347
00:20:55,025 --> 00:20:56,568
The sender was unknown.

348
00:20:57,194 --> 00:20:59,780
But obviously, it's someone
who wants to attack you.

349
00:20:59,863 --> 00:21:01,406
Of course, it's a setup.

350
00:21:01,490 --> 00:21:04,493
Do I look like someone
who would accept a bribe?

351
00:21:04,576 --> 00:21:08,497
Right. It would be clumsy of you
to accept it so openly.

352
00:21:08,580 --> 00:21:09,915
Of course. How would I…

353
00:21:12,167 --> 00:21:13,001
Wait a second.

354
00:21:14,044 --> 00:21:17,214
You think of me as someone
who does accept bribes then?

355
00:21:17,297 --> 00:21:20,092
I rewatched it several times
because it didn't make sense.

356
00:21:20,175 --> 00:21:23,011
But no matter how I look at it,
it was you.

357
00:21:23,095 --> 00:21:24,721
And there's no trace of manipulation.

358
00:21:26,390 --> 00:21:27,808
I'm disappointed, Ms. Park.

359
00:21:28,975 --> 00:21:30,394
-Disappointed?
-Yes.

360
00:21:30,477 --> 00:21:32,687
Based on that single uncertain video,

361
00:21:32,771 --> 00:21:35,232
you suddenly started
to treat me as a criminal?

362
00:21:36,149 --> 00:21:37,776
Where's the benefit of the doubt?

363
00:21:38,944 --> 00:21:40,987
You're making light of something serious.

364
00:21:41,071 --> 00:21:42,030
In what way?

365
00:21:42,114 --> 00:21:44,032
Isn't it suspicious
based on the situation?

366
00:21:44,116 --> 00:21:45,409
In what way?

367
00:21:45,492 --> 00:21:47,911
-I'm not just talking about the video.
-Then what?

368
00:21:47,994 --> 00:21:50,288
You don't have any interest
in pro bono cases.

369
00:21:50,372 --> 00:21:53,542
But you suddenly quit as a prominent judge
to be a pro bono attorney?

370
00:21:54,292 --> 00:21:55,961
You don't think that's weird?

371
00:21:56,044 --> 00:21:58,797
You shouldn't misinterpret
someone's goodwill.

372
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:02,217
I'm using my experience and skills
to help the socially disadvantaged--

373
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:05,345
You made a deal
with a 70% winning rate as a condition.

374
00:22:05,429 --> 00:22:08,140
My goodness, you didn't know?

375
00:22:08,223 --> 00:22:09,850
He proposed a 70% winning rate.

376
00:22:11,518 --> 00:22:14,813
In return, he wants a recommendation
to be a justice candidate next year.

377
00:22:14,896 --> 00:22:18,400
I'll disband Team Pro Bono
if he can't maintain that condition.

378
00:22:22,112 --> 00:22:24,531
I didn't know we were working hard

379
00:22:24,614 --> 00:22:28,827
to win the bet you made
to become a Supreme Court justice.

380
00:22:28,910 --> 00:22:33,540
I said that to show I'd do my best--

381
00:22:33,623 --> 00:22:34,583
I…

382
00:22:36,918 --> 00:22:38,253
I still want to believe

383
00:22:39,921 --> 00:22:41,965
that you're a good person.

384
00:22:42,048 --> 00:22:43,300
What?

385
00:22:43,383 --> 00:22:46,303
You look sincere in court
when you make your arguments.

386
00:22:48,763 --> 00:22:51,349
But if the others on the team find out,

387
00:22:52,601 --> 00:22:55,604
I don't know
if they will still believe in you.

388
00:22:55,687 --> 00:22:58,857
-Nan-hui didn't like you in the first--
-Why should I care?

389
00:22:59,482 --> 00:23:01,651
-What?
-Think whatever you want.

390
00:23:01,735 --> 00:23:05,030
I don't care about
what others think of me.

391
00:23:05,113 --> 00:23:08,033
Whatever my intention is,
I can just win for you guys.

392
00:23:08,116 --> 00:23:10,619
Is it fun to win only 20% of the time?
You like that?

393
00:23:11,536 --> 00:23:14,748
I mean, losing isn't your hobby. Right?

394
00:23:18,084 --> 00:23:21,463
We've done enough team building
for today, so I'll get going.

395
00:23:22,172 --> 00:23:24,925
I'll pay for what I ate,
so don't worry about it.

396
00:23:45,654 --> 00:23:48,490
Hello, everyone!

397
00:23:49,032 --> 00:23:51,326
Hey, we won. What's with this vibe?

398
00:23:51,409 --> 00:23:52,911
DEFENDANT CHO SUBMITS APPEAL

399
00:23:52,994 --> 00:23:54,287
-What?
-What is it?

400
00:23:55,038 --> 00:23:57,332
Mr. Woo submitted an appeal.

401
00:23:57,415 --> 00:24:00,377
Really? My goodness.

402
00:24:00,460 --> 00:24:02,796
He's a passionate guy
who doesn't know how to give up.

403
00:24:02,879 --> 00:24:04,297
It's because he gets too obsessed.

404
00:24:05,548 --> 00:24:07,342
Runner-ups are always like that.

405
00:24:08,551 --> 00:24:10,470
What argument
is he going to make this time?

406
00:24:11,054 --> 00:24:12,681
-Will it be okay?
-Will it be all right?

407
00:24:12,764 --> 00:24:16,059
The case already has a touching story.

408
00:24:16,142 --> 00:24:16,977
Here.

409
00:24:18,436 --> 00:24:19,354
Look.

410
00:24:19,437 --> 00:24:22,774
How could he beat this?
He's just being a sore loser.

411
00:24:22,857 --> 00:24:24,067
That must be it.

412
00:24:24,150 --> 00:24:26,987
And what's there to worry about
when we have Mr. Kang?

413
00:24:27,487 --> 00:24:28,530
Of course.

414
00:24:29,364 --> 00:24:31,950
-Gosh, I hate him.
-Here. Look.

415
00:24:34,911 --> 00:24:37,205
SUWON FAMILY COURT,
APPELLATE COURT

416
00:24:37,289 --> 00:24:38,206
Ms. Kaya,

417
00:24:39,207 --> 00:24:40,667
after that man kidnapped you,

418
00:24:41,251 --> 00:24:43,420
how long did you stay at his house?

419
00:24:44,337 --> 00:24:45,755
For about nine months.

420
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:48,633
That's almost a year.

421
00:24:48,717 --> 00:24:50,885
During that long period of time,

422
00:24:50,969 --> 00:24:54,139
were you confined
in some kind of locked room?

423
00:24:56,933 --> 00:24:58,435
-No.
-Really?

424
00:24:59,394 --> 00:25:01,062
Then, why didn't you run away?

425
00:25:01,813 --> 00:25:05,859
Did the man treat you so well
that you didn't miss your mom?

426
00:25:06,359 --> 00:25:07,569
Your Honor.

427
00:25:07,652 --> 00:25:10,071
Mr. Woo, please be mindful
of your wording.

428
00:25:10,155 --> 00:25:11,906
Yes, I will, Your Honor.

429
00:25:11,990 --> 00:25:13,658
Ms. Kaya, let me ask you again.

430
00:25:14,576 --> 00:25:16,619
Why didn't you run away?

431
00:25:16,703 --> 00:25:18,204
I did.

432
00:25:27,547 --> 00:25:28,882
A week after I was kidnapped.

433
00:25:28,965 --> 00:25:33,219
And then, after that,
you came back to the man's house.

434
00:25:33,970 --> 00:25:35,347
You came back voluntarily?

435
00:25:35,430 --> 00:25:38,099
I didn't go back because I wanted to!

436
00:25:42,187 --> 00:25:45,482
My child! You must've been so scared.

437
00:25:45,565 --> 00:25:48,193
Mom…

438
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:52,197
Mom…

439
00:25:52,280 --> 00:25:53,114
Go back!

440
00:25:53,782 --> 00:25:56,242
-Dad.
-You've already lost your worth

441
00:25:56,326 --> 00:25:58,661
and dignity as a girl.

442
00:25:58,745 --> 00:26:00,330
Do you understand that?

443
00:26:01,289 --> 00:26:04,876
Who would ever marry you in now?
There is nothing we can do.

444
00:26:05,668 --> 00:26:07,754
When he comes,
go live with him in his village.

445
00:26:07,837 --> 00:26:09,798
-Honey!
-You be quiet!

446
00:26:09,881 --> 00:26:11,925
-Dad!
-Go back! Get out!

447
00:26:12,550 --> 00:26:14,302
Mom, please help me!

448
00:26:14,886 --> 00:26:16,763
Mom, I don't want to go!

449
00:26:17,430 --> 00:26:18,932
Mom, I'm scared!

450
00:26:19,724 --> 00:26:20,934
Mom!

451
00:26:21,017 --> 00:26:25,188
Your parents sent you back to him.

452
00:26:25,271 --> 00:26:27,190
"Go live with him in his village."

453
00:26:28,358 --> 00:26:30,860
Isn't that an approval
of the marriage then?

454
00:26:33,154 --> 00:26:34,114
Right?

455
00:26:36,116 --> 00:26:36,950
Marriage?

456
00:26:37,867 --> 00:26:41,079
You call that marriage?

457
00:26:41,162 --> 00:26:44,416
Isn't it? You lived at your in-laws' house
with permission from your parents.

458
00:26:44,499 --> 00:26:48,753
That man hit me every day!

459
00:26:51,339 --> 00:26:52,549
And every night…

460
00:26:56,177 --> 00:26:57,345
I was violated.

461
00:26:59,973 --> 00:27:03,560
I was only 13 years old, sir.

462
00:27:03,643 --> 00:27:06,771
Still, if you lived with him
for nine months,

463
00:27:06,855 --> 00:27:10,108
wouldn't you say
you had a stable relationship?

464
00:27:16,489 --> 00:27:18,491
I ran away again

465
00:27:18,575 --> 00:27:20,326
after nine months.

466
00:27:20,827 --> 00:27:22,370
What about the childbirth?

467
00:27:22,454 --> 00:27:25,331
-You didn't give birth at his house?
-No!

468
00:27:30,420 --> 00:27:36,134
I couldn't live in that hell anymore,

469
00:27:36,217 --> 00:27:38,720
so I ran away and went back home!

470
00:27:42,098 --> 00:27:44,142
While I was pregnant.

471
00:27:44,809 --> 00:27:47,687
Did you give birth at your home then?

472
00:27:52,567 --> 00:27:53,568
No.

473
00:27:54,819 --> 00:27:55,778
Why not?

474
00:28:01,576 --> 00:28:06,331
Mom, Dad!
Open the door for me, please!

475
00:28:06,414 --> 00:28:08,666
-My child!
-Mom!

476
00:28:08,750 --> 00:28:09,834
My child, are you okay?

477
00:28:10,418 --> 00:28:11,878
Honey!

478
00:28:11,961 --> 00:28:13,421
-Go back now!
-Dad!

479
00:28:13,505 --> 00:28:16,341
Why didn't you listen to me?
Why did you decide to come back?

480
00:28:16,424 --> 00:28:17,675
With that body of yours,

481
00:28:18,426 --> 00:28:20,303
it will bring us bad luck! Go back now!

482
00:28:20,386 --> 00:28:21,221
Go! Get out!

483
00:28:22,388 --> 00:28:23,473
My child!

484
00:28:23,556 --> 00:28:25,600
Mom! Dad!

485
00:28:26,226 --> 00:28:27,393
Mom!

486
00:28:28,019 --> 00:28:29,229
My father

487
00:28:30,313 --> 00:28:32,565
didn't let me back in the house.

488
00:28:36,486 --> 00:28:37,695
I…

489
00:28:38,488 --> 00:28:41,699
I gave birth there…

490
00:28:44,536 --> 00:28:46,329
KAYA

491
00:28:47,622 --> 00:28:49,541
…with the help of others.

492
00:28:52,460 --> 00:28:53,294
I see.

493
00:28:55,463 --> 00:28:56,464
Okay.

494
00:28:57,632 --> 00:28:58,925
Thank you, Ms. Kaya.

495
00:29:00,176 --> 00:29:01,386
Nothing further, Your Honor.

496
00:29:19,571 --> 00:29:21,447
The Court will deliver the verdict.

497
00:29:22,657 --> 00:29:25,076
According to the proceedings
of this appeal case,

498
00:29:25,159 --> 00:29:29,372
it is true that the plaintiff
was kidnapped and sexually abused,

499
00:29:29,455 --> 00:29:33,918
but it is also true she lived with the man
for approximately nine months.

500
00:29:35,211 --> 00:29:36,629
-However…
-However…

501
00:29:36,713 --> 00:29:40,967
Moreover,
considering the date of childbirth,

502
00:29:41,050 --> 00:29:43,553
the plaintiff became pregnant

503
00:29:44,178 --> 00:29:46,347
not during the first time
she was kidnapped

504
00:29:46,431 --> 00:29:48,641
but during the time she lived with the man

505
00:29:48,725 --> 00:29:51,144
under the permission of her parents.

506
00:29:52,228 --> 00:29:54,314
No way.

507
00:29:54,397 --> 00:29:56,357
Considering all of these circumstances,

508
00:29:56,441 --> 00:30:00,486
it is hard to say
the plaintiff's pregnancy and childbirth

509
00:30:00,570 --> 00:30:02,822
seriously harmed her reputation.

510
00:30:02,906 --> 00:30:04,282
That's nonsense!

511
00:30:04,365 --> 00:30:07,118
-Bailiff.
-Yes, Your Honor. Please be seated.

512
00:30:08,703 --> 00:30:10,038
We will continue.

513
00:30:10,955 --> 00:30:13,958
Thus, compelling the plaintiff
to bear the duty of disclosing such facts

514
00:30:14,042 --> 00:30:16,502
does not excessively infringe
on her right to privacy

515
00:30:16,586 --> 00:30:18,588
and freedom of private life.

516
00:30:19,505 --> 00:30:22,133
The act of not disclosing
her history of childbirth

517
00:30:22,216 --> 00:30:24,093
is a cause for annulling the marriage.

518
00:30:26,012 --> 00:30:28,389
