652
00:38:33,040 --> 00:38:34,041
Oh, no.

653
00:38:44,093 --> 00:38:45,010
Mr. Kang.

654
00:38:45,636 --> 00:38:46,762
Mr. Kang?

655
00:38:48,597 --> 00:38:50,599
-Mr. Kang!
-Where are you going?

656
00:39:20,754 --> 00:39:24,842
For the first time in my life,
someone stood up for me.

657
00:39:25,551 --> 00:39:29,763
And it was in this faraway land
where I'm a foreigner.

658
00:39:34,518 --> 00:39:38,355
In my address to the UN General Assembly
to celebrate World Refugee Day,

659
00:39:38,439 --> 00:39:42,443
I will proudly illustrate
how Korea will lead the world

660
00:39:42,526 --> 00:39:46,363
not only in economy and culture
but also in human rights--

661
