00:46:15,085 --> 00:46:19,423
Then, why on earth did you apply
for refugee status so absurdly…

775
00:46:19,506 --> 00:46:21,049
Asylum?

776
00:46:22,426 --> 00:46:23,635
Where?

777
00:46:23,719 --> 00:46:26,221
America? France?

778
00:46:26,305 --> 00:46:29,683
Why does she seek refuge in Korea?

779
00:46:30,309 --> 00:46:33,103
You said she was persecuted in Korea.

780
00:46:33,186 --> 00:46:34,563
Then of course,

781
00:46:34,646 --> 00:46:37,316
common sense would be
to seek refugee status

782
00:46:37,399 --> 00:46:40,193
or asylum in a different country.

783
00:46:40,277 --> 00:46:43,363
Why is she seeking asylum
in the Republic of Korea?

784
00:46:48,243 --> 00:46:50,996
-Is that the real Republic of Korea?
-What?

785
00:46:51,079 --> 00:46:55,250
Your Honor, I'm asking
the judiciary of the Republic of Korea.

786
00:46:55,334 --> 00:46:59,046
A country that releases offenders
of sexual assault and deports the victims.

787
00:46:59,963 --> 00:47:02,132
A country that treats someone
as a marriage scammer

788
00:47:02,215 --> 00:47:04,426
for hiding her past
as a child sexual abuse victim.

789
00:47:04,509 --> 00:47:07,179
Is that kind of country
the real Republic of Korea?

790
00:47:07,846 --> 00:47:10,140
After being a leader
in economy and culture,

791
00:47:10,223 --> 00:47:13,560
this country now boasts to the world
of being a leader in human rights.

792
00:47:13,644 --> 00:47:16,063
That is the Republic of Korea I know.

793
00:47:16,980 --> 00:47:18,690
Your Honor, don't tell me

794
00:47:19,399 --> 00:47:22,819
you acknowledge that barbaric country

795
00:47:22,903 --> 00:47:27,991
that trampled on the plaintiff's dignity
as the Republic of Korea, do you?

796
00:47:28,075 --> 00:47:28,992
Your Honor,

797
00:47:29,076 --> 00:47:32,287
the plaintiff's counsel is employing
ridiculous and misleading arguments.

798
00:47:32,371 --> 00:47:35,791
If this country isn't Korea,
then where on earth are we?

799
00:47:36,917 --> 00:47:40,587
Then, let me use the legal reasoning
that the defendant's counsel loves.

800
00:47:41,546 --> 00:47:44,716
According to the Constitution,
the territory of the Republic of Korea

801
00:47:44,800 --> 00:47:47,761
consists of the Korean peninsula
and all of its adjacent islands.

802
00:47:47,844 --> 00:47:50,263
It's just that the territory
north of the MDL

803
00:47:50,347 --> 00:47:53,100
is effectively occupied
by the North Korean government,

804
00:47:53,183 --> 00:47:55,519
a legally defined
anti-government organization.

805
00:47:55,602 --> 00:48:00,315
As you can see, different countries
can exist within Korean territory.

806
00:48:00,399 --> 00:48:04,236
A country that neglects victims
and is generous only to assailants.

807
00:48:05,028 --> 00:48:07,864
A country that ignores the powerless
and protects the powerful.

808
00:48:08,615 --> 00:48:12,160
A country of assailants,
their protectors, and bystanders.

809
00:48:13,036 --> 00:48:16,873
Surely, that can't be
all there is in Korea.

810
00:48:16,957 --> 00:48:20,377
They're just occupying
a part of the territory effectively.

811
00:48:21,044 --> 00:48:24,923
Because Kaya was persecuted
in that barbaric country,

812
00:48:25,507 --> 00:48:28,719
we go to the only legal government
in this territory,

813
00:48:28,802 --> 00:48:32,472
and we seek asylum
in the free and just Republic of Korea.

814
00:48:40,814 --> 00:48:43,316
Which version of Korea is yours,
Your Honor?

815
00:48:44,860 --> 00:48:49,614
Which country's judiciary are you part of?

816
00:48:50,449 --> 00:48:52,159
Mr. Kang!

817
00:48:58,373 --> 00:48:59,541
We will take a brief recess.

818
00:49:00,625 --> 00:49:03,879
Both counsels,
I want to see you in my chambers.

819
00:49:05,505 --> 00:49:07,090
All rise.

820
00:49:13,054 --> 00:49:14,473
We're coming in, sir.

821
00:49:23,899 --> 00:49:25,567
Judge Kang Da-wit!

822
00:49:26,359 --> 00:49:28,653
I'm an attorney now, Your Honor.

823
00:49:28,737 --> 00:49:32,491
For someone who used to be a judge,
what on earth are you doing?

824
00:49:32,574 --> 00:49:35,911
I've served this country
my entire life as a patriot.

825
00:49:35,994 --> 00:49:39,498
And now, all I'm waiting for
is the day I can honorably retire!

826
00:49:40,081 --> 00:49:43,293
Do you expect me
to play along in this clown show?

827
00:49:43,376 --> 00:49:45,587
A clown show?

828
00:49:45,670 --> 00:49:49,299
Sure, I may be a clown.

829
00:49:50,217 --> 00:49:52,302
But this trial isn't a clown show.

830
00:49:52,844 --> 00:49:55,597
It's a desperate fight.

831
00:49:58,683 --> 00:49:59,601
Your Honor.

832
00:50:01,770 --> 00:50:02,979
Are you sure

833
00:50:03,647 --> 00:50:05,732
this is a trial you're trying to win?

834
00:50:07,359 --> 00:50:11,530
Isn't this just a trial you're using
to publicly embarrass the country?

835
00:50:11,613 --> 00:50:14,157
You have a horde of reporters
in the first row!

836
00:50:14,241 --> 00:50:17,494
You keep saying "Republic of Korea"!

837
00:50:18,370 --> 00:50:21,581
What are you trying to do
by exposing my country's flaws?

838
00:50:21,665 --> 00:50:25,085
Don't you have
the slightest bit of patriotism?

839
00:50:25,168 --> 00:50:28,046
He's always been someone
who'd do anything to win.

840
00:50:28,129 --> 00:50:30,048
This ridiculous trial is…

841
00:50:31,216 --> 00:50:33,426
Please end it immediately, Your Honor.

842
00:50:35,971 --> 00:50:39,224
I started this trial
because I believe in my country.

843
00:50:39,307 --> 00:50:42,310
If you end this trial
before giving us a chance to fight,

844
00:50:42,394 --> 00:50:45,522
can I take that as you running away
because you're scared of me?

845
00:50:49,442 --> 00:50:52,112
Someone as yourself who served
in the almighty Marine Corps?

846
00:50:52,195 --> 00:50:53,655
Come on. No way.

847
00:50:56,199 --> 00:50:58,076
What did you just say?

848
00:50:59,160 --> 00:51:02,163
Come here. Come out from there!

849
00:51:06,668 --> 00:51:07,961
Are you okay?

850
00:51:08,044 --> 00:51:11,131
Judge Cho Gang-yeol is infamous
for being hot-tempered and stubborn.

851
00:51:11,214 --> 00:51:13,800
He didn't kick you or anything, did he?

852
00:51:13,884 --> 00:51:16,052
Gosh, I would appreciate that.

853
00:51:16,136 --> 00:51:19,097
I'd throw myself on the floor,
sue the country for compensation,

854
00:51:19,180 --> 00:51:20,807
and broadcast it live.

855
00:51:20,891 --> 00:51:25,854
I'm glad the trial got a continuance,
but will it be okay?

856
00:51:26,563 --> 00:51:30,567
Mentally, I agree 100% with you
in your argument.

857
00:51:31,067 --> 00:51:32,444
-But legally…
-Of course…

858
00:51:34,154 --> 00:51:35,488
Of course, we'll lose.

859
00:51:35,572 --> 00:51:37,032
What? If you know that, then why…

860
00:51:37,115 --> 00:51:40,410
You said there are trials you have to do
despite knowing that you'll lose.

861
00:51:41,286 --> 00:51:44,414
You said that's the job
of a pro bono attorney.

862
00:51:46,875 --> 00:51:48,126
Well…

863
00:51:48,209 --> 00:51:52,005
After making precedents by fighting
in trials that are hard to win,

864
00:51:52,088 --> 00:51:53,757
we can change the world one day.

865
00:51:53,840 --> 00:51:55,342
That's what I meant.

866
00:51:55,425 --> 00:51:56,509
Right now, Kaya needs--

867
00:51:56,593 --> 00:51:59,387
I'm not interested in changing the world.

868
00:51:59,471 --> 00:52:03,600
-I'm only interested in winning my case.
-You said we'd lose.

869
00:52:03,683 --> 00:52:07,103
We'd lose the trial,
but we'll win the case.

870
00:52:08,146 --> 00:52:10,774
At the very least, time is on our side.

871
00:52:11,566 --> 00:52:12,817
What do you mean?

872
00:52:14,736 --> 00:52:16,196
It's in a month and a half.

873
00:52:16,821 --> 00:52:18,114
World Refugee Day.

874
00:52:22,661 --> 00:52:23,745
World Refugee Day.

875
00:52:23,828 --> 00:52:26,623
President Choi Yeong-seop
will deliver a historic speech

876
00:52:26,706 --> 00:52:27,791
at the UN General Assembly.

877
00:52:29,000 --> 00:52:30,001
The president.

878
00:52:31,211 --> 00:52:32,045
The UN speech!

879
00:52:32,128 --> 00:52:34,631
I've contacted every reporter I know,

880
00:52:34,714 --> 00:52:36,925
so news should be flooding
the internet by now.

881
00:52:37,008 --> 00:52:40,220
This will rock the Ministry of Justice,
which is the ministry in charge.

882
00:52:40,303 --> 00:52:42,931
The President is on course
to embarrass himself at the UN.

883
00:52:44,015 --> 00:52:45,475
They'll ask for a deal.

884
00:52:46,142 --> 00:52:50,313
The key to this trial
is to stir up the world,

885
00:52:50,981 --> 00:52:52,065
so they can't ignore it.

886
00:52:54,401 --> 00:52:55,902
You're quick, Ms. Park.

887
00:52:56,695 --> 00:52:58,196
All right, everyone. Do you remember?

888
00:52:58,279 --> 00:53:01,700
The last scene
of Ms. Park's favorite courtroom film?

889
00:53:02,283 --> 00:53:03,785
What? What is it?

890
00:53:08,289 --> 00:53:11,710
Okay. I will now call out the names.

891
00:53:13,044 --> 00:53:14,254
Attorney Kang Da-wit.

892
00:53:16,006 --> 00:53:18,591
Present. I'll get going first.

893
00:53:18,675 --> 00:53:19,676
What?

894
00:53:20,844 --> 00:53:22,595
Attorney Jang Yeong-sil.

895
00:53:22,679 --> 00:53:25,306
Present. I'll get going too.

896
00:53:25,390 --> 00:53:28,309
Where on earth are you going?

897
00:53:28,393 --> 00:53:29,728
Attorney Hwang Jun-u.

898
00:53:31,646 --> 00:53:32,480
What?

899
00:53:32,981 --> 00:53:34,315
Take good care of the office.

900
00:53:34,399 --> 00:53:36,693
Okay. Wait, no.

901
00:53:37,277 --> 00:53:38,987
Gi-ppeum, where are you going?

902
00:53:39,070 --> 00:53:41,072
What movie is it?

903
00:53:50,123 --> 00:53:51,332
You may be seated.

904
00:53:56,463 --> 00:53:58,381
What is going on?

905
00:53:58,465 --> 00:54:02,218
Why are there so many attorneys here?

906
00:54:02,844 --> 00:54:05,055
Attorney Han, what is going on?

907
00:54:05,138 --> 00:54:06,264
Your Honor.

908
00:54:06,347 --> 00:54:09,976
We're attorneys from the public interest
and human rights foundation Donggam.

909
00:54:10,769 --> 00:54:15,815
As we agree with the intent of this trial,
we have joined as co-counsels.

910
00:54:17,901 --> 00:54:20,820
We're attorneys
from the nonprofit organization Neolli.

911
00:54:20,904 --> 00:54:24,324
We would also like to join as co-counsels.

912
00:54:24,949 --> 00:54:27,494
We're attorneys from the foundation
Gyeongcheon, Your Honor.

913
00:54:28,119 --> 00:54:32,373
The clients we have represented
are here in this courtroom today.

914
00:54:32,999 --> 00:54:36,753
They are the victims of the country

915
00:54:37,420 --> 00:54:39,214
that persecuted the plaintiff Kaya.

916
00:54:40,090 --> 00:54:42,634
May I request a moment for them to speak?

917
00:54:46,096 --> 00:54:46,930
Go ahead.

918
00:54:55,480 --> 00:54:57,398
I'm a victim of dating abuse.

919
00:54:59,150 --> 00:55:01,152
I mustered the courage to report it,

920
00:55:02,153 --> 00:55:06,533
but the police forced me to settle,
saying it was a matter between lovers.

921
00:55:09,953 --> 00:55:12,455
I'm a victim
of workplace sexual harassment.

922
00:55:14,040 --> 00:55:17,502
The assailant, who was my superior,
said he was drunk and avoided punishment.

923
00:55:17,585 --> 00:55:21,214
After raising the issue, only I was fired.

924
00:55:24,384 --> 00:55:25,218
I'm…

925
00:55:28,680 --> 00:55:30,515
I am a victim of child sexual abuse.

926
00:55:32,350 --> 00:55:35,061
That horrifying memory
is still vivid in my mind.

927
00:55:36,020 --> 00:55:39,691
But that monster has already been released
and moved to a neighborhood nearby mine.

928
00:55:43,236 --> 00:55:44,696
What kind of country is this?

929
00:55:47,740 --> 00:55:50,076
In addition to these people,

930
00:55:51,035 --> 00:55:55,540
numerous people have been victimized
like Kaya by this barbaric country.

931
00:56:00,170 --> 00:56:02,338
Our group of attorneys feels the same way.

932
00:56:02,422 --> 00:56:06,092
No longer do we want to live in a country

933
00:56:06,801 --> 00:56:08,845
that ignores victims

934
00:56:10,346 --> 00:56:11,806
and protects assailants.

935
00:56:16,144 --> 00:56:17,478
Your Honor,

936
00:56:18,396 --> 00:56:22,317
please accept our application
for asylum from everyone here.

937
00:56:23,401 --> 00:56:25,612
-Please accept it.
-Please accept it.

938
00:56:34,621 --> 00:56:37,373
The Pro Bono Avengers
are pretty incredible.

939
00:56:37,457 --> 00:56:39,542
They're all experienced fighters.

940
00:56:42,629 --> 00:56:44,547
All right, I understand.

941
00:56:44,631 --> 00:56:45,590
So please be seated.

942
00:56:46,216 --> 00:56:48,426
Plaintiff's counsel, please continue.

943
00:56:48,509 --> 00:56:49,761
Your Honor,

944
00:56:49,844 --> 00:56:53,264
these people here aren't the only ones
who are applying for refugee status.

945
00:56:54,599 --> 00:56:57,185
Please accept my application for asylum!

946
00:56:58,394 --> 00:57:02,106
WE SEEK ASYLUM
REFUGEES ARE PEOPLE TOO

947
00:57:02,190 --> 00:57:08,863
-We seek asylum!
-We seek asylum!

948
00:57:11,699 --> 00:57:12,700
Wait.

949
00:57:13,534 --> 00:57:16,746
There are this many angry people
who are willing

950
00:57:17,413 --> 00:57:18,998
to make themselves refugees?

951
00:57:19,082 --> 00:57:21,876
Your Honor, the plaintiff is trying
to hold a trial by media

952
00:57:21,960 --> 00:57:24,128
by dragging in external forces.

953
00:57:24,212 --> 00:57:27,715
They're making all this chaos
for just one foreign woman.

954
00:57:28,299 --> 00:57:31,761
This trial is an embarrassment to Korea
that harms national interest--

955
00:57:31,844 --> 00:57:33,304
One foreign woman?

956
00:57:33,388 --> 00:57:34,430
Am I wrong?

957
00:57:34,514 --> 00:57:37,141
Does defense counsel still think
this doesn't concern you?

958
00:57:38,476 --> 00:57:42,730
This can happen to anyone, not just Kaya.

959
00:57:42,814 --> 00:57:43,731
It's a case

960
00:57:43,815 --> 00:57:46,150
where universal women's rights
were violated.

961
00:57:47,902 --> 00:57:49,904
You said it harms national interest?

962
00:57:51,990 --> 00:57:53,116
Look at the photos.

963
00:57:54,951 --> 00:57:57,579
Foreign workers working in factories.

964
00:57:57,662 --> 00:58:00,164
Foreign daughters-in-law working on farms.

965
00:58:00,915 --> 00:58:04,294
These people came from far away

966
00:58:04,377 --> 00:58:07,630
to take care of the farms
that we abandoned.

967
00:58:12,552 --> 00:58:13,386
Your Honor,

968
00:58:14,721 --> 00:58:17,348
we're living in a global world

969
00:58:17,432 --> 00:58:21,185
where it's meaningless
to talk about nationalities.

970
00:58:23,187 --> 00:58:24,564
Goodness, today,

971
00:58:24,647 --> 00:58:28,735
we have attorneys
from big firms here en masse.

972
00:58:29,277 --> 00:58:30,236
Mr. Woo.

973
00:58:30,320 --> 00:58:33,281
All of your children
are US citizens, aren't they?

974
00:58:33,990 --> 00:58:34,824
Congratulations.

975
00:58:34,907 --> 00:58:38,620
Going to New York every time to give birth
must have been really tough.

976
00:58:40,288 --> 00:58:43,124
Mr. Jeong, I heard you earned
Dominican citizenship recently.

977
00:58:45,001 --> 00:58:47,003
I heard they don't pay taxes there.

978
00:58:47,587 --> 00:58:49,797
Mr. Pyo and Mr. Ju.

979
00:58:49,881 --> 00:58:50,965
Your children have attended

980
00:58:51,049 --> 00:58:52,634
international schools
since kindergarten

981
00:58:52,717 --> 00:58:53,593
and now study abroad.

982
00:58:53,676 --> 00:58:57,472
Both of you are preparing
to immigrate as well.

983
00:58:57,555 --> 00:58:59,682
What on earth are you doing, Mr. Kang?

984
00:58:59,766 --> 00:59:01,434
I'm really curious.

985
00:59:01,517 --> 00:59:04,103
Black-haired foreigners

986
00:59:04,187 --> 00:59:07,440
who were born in New York and LA
and briefly come to Korea

987
00:59:08,191 --> 00:59:10,151
during vacations.

988
00:59:10,818 --> 00:59:12,111
And Koreans from faraway places

989
00:59:12,195 --> 00:59:15,114
who take care of our farms,
fishing villages, and factories

990
00:59:15,198 --> 00:59:17,283
as they work hard to learn Korean

991
00:59:17,367 --> 00:59:19,869
while being ignored by our citizens.

992
00:59:20,495 --> 00:59:23,373
Between these two,
who are the real members of this country?

993
00:59:26,959 --> 00:59:29,087
He said earlier this was
an embarrassment to Korea

994
00:59:29,170 --> 00:59:31,214
and it harms national interest.

995
00:59:31,923 --> 00:59:35,385
In whose interest is that for?

996
00:59:39,305 --> 00:59:40,598
Your Honor,

997
00:59:40,682 --> 00:59:45,186
who lives in that Republic of Korea?

998
00:59:49,774 --> 00:59:50,775
Which country

999
00:59:52,568 --> 00:59:54,320
are we living in right now?

1000
00:59:59,575 --> 01:00:01,619
Are you done with your arguments, Counsel?

1001
01:00:06,749 --> 01:00:08,918
Yes. I rest my case, Your Honor.

1002
01:00:10,086 --> 01:00:12,630
The Court will close
the arguments of this case.

1003
01:00:12,714 --> 01:00:16,509
We will deliver the verdict in two weeks.

1004
01:00:21,597 --> 01:00:25,017
In whose interest is that for?

1005
01:00:37,739 --> 01:00:39,157
Your Honor,

1006
01:00:39,240 --> 01:00:42,326
who lives in that Republic of Korea?

1007
01:00:42,410 --> 01:00:44,579
CERTIFICATE OF MERIT

1008
01:00:47,582 --> 01:00:50,418
SEOUL ADMINISTRATIVE COURT

1009
01:00:50,501 --> 01:00:51,461
Please be seated.

1010
01:01:02,972 --> 01:01:06,476
I've had many thoughts
before arriving at a judgment.

1011
01:01:07,393 --> 01:01:11,564
To be honest, this was the first time
in my 35 years as a judge

1012
01:01:11,647 --> 01:01:16,027
to preside over a case
with such ridiculous legal arguments.

1013
01:01:16,736 --> 01:01:20,198
The plaintiff's counsel asked me

1014
01:01:20,948 --> 01:01:23,409
which version of Korea was mine

1015
01:01:23,493 --> 01:01:27,330
and which country's judiciary
I was a part of.

1016
01:01:28,956 --> 01:01:30,958
This is a personal story,

1017
01:01:32,126 --> 01:01:35,630
so I'm sorry and embarrassed to say,

1018
01:01:35,713 --> 01:01:37,548
but even after passing national exams,

1019
01:01:37,632 --> 01:01:41,844
I've been proud my entire life
that I voluntarily enlisted and worked

1020
01:01:41,928 --> 01:01:44,555
as an ordinary soldier
in the Marine Corps.

1021
01:01:45,515 --> 01:01:48,434
My grandfather died in Manchuria

1022
01:01:48,518 --> 01:01:51,270
while fighting the Japanese
as a soldier in the independence army.

1023
01:01:51,354 --> 01:01:55,316
My father died in the streets
during the April Revolution

1024
01:01:55,399 --> 01:01:58,236
while resisting the dictatorship.

1025
01:01:59,320 --> 01:02:03,533
I have given it a lot of thought
throughout the trial.

1026
01:02:04,450 --> 01:02:07,662
What kind of country is the Korea

1027
01:02:07,745 --> 01:02:11,082
that three generations of my family
have protected with their lives?

1028
01:02:12,834 --> 01:02:16,838
No matter how much I think about it,
one thing is clear.

1029
01:02:19,048 --> 01:02:20,675
The lousy country

1030
01:02:20,758 --> 01:02:24,095
that so cruelly and shamelessly
pushed away and persecuted

1031
01:02:24,637 --> 01:02:28,808
a young person who came all the way here

1032
01:02:28,891 --> 01:02:30,268
to pursue her dreams…

1033
01:02:31,936 --> 01:02:33,855
That is not my Korea.

1034
01:02:35,398 --> 01:02:39,277
Instead of a country of assailants,
their protectors, and bystanders,

1035
01:02:39,360 --> 01:02:41,654
you said she seeks asylum

1036
01:02:41,737 --> 01:02:44,073
in the only legal government
in this territory,

1037
01:02:44,156 --> 01:02:46,409
the free and just Republic of Korea?

1038
01:02:47,410 --> 01:02:49,328
No matter how much I think about it,

1039
01:02:50,204 --> 01:02:52,290
for the past 35 years,

1040
01:02:52,957 --> 01:02:55,209
I believe I've worked as a judge

1041
01:02:55,793 --> 01:02:59,046
in that free and just Republic of Korea.

1042
01:03:00,089 --> 01:03:02,633
-No way.
-Damn it.

1043
01:03:02,717 --> 01:03:04,719
The Court will deliver the verdict.

1044
01:03:07,263 --> 01:03:10,099
This Court hereby rules

1045
01:03:11,017 --> 01:03:14,103
that the defendant's denial
of the plaintiff's refugee status

1046
01:03:14,186 --> 01:03:16,355
-is hereby annulled.
-Yes!

1047
01:03:16,439 --> 01:03:19,525
The defendant will bear
the cost of the lawsuit.

1048
01:03:20,234 --> 01:03:21,903
Yeah!

1049
01:03:26,365 --> 01:03:28,034
Excuse me, Your Honor.

1050
01:03:28,117 --> 01:03:29,744
All rise.

1051
01:03:30,620 --> 01:03:31,579
Your Honor!

1052
01:03:33,956 --> 01:03:34,790
Ms. Kaya.

1053
01:03:37,418 --> 01:03:38,544
Yes, Your Honor?

1054
01:03:39,670 --> 01:03:41,172
It's been hard, hasn't it?

1055
01:03:42,506 --> 01:03:43,758
I'm sorry.

1056
01:03:46,218 --> 01:03:47,762
And thank you

1057
01:03:47,845 --> 01:03:49,597
for coming to Korea.

1058
01:04:23,339 --> 01:04:26,968
With a historic UN speech
on World Refugee Day approaching,

1059
01:04:27,051 --> 01:04:29,220
the aftermath
of the so-called "asylum verdict"

1060
01:04:29,303 --> 01:04:31,222
has put the Blue House in an awkward spot.

1061
01:04:31,305 --> 01:04:32,306
As for now,

1062
01:04:32,390 --> 01:04:36,811
I don't think it's a case
that we need to comment on.

1063
01:04:36,894 --> 01:04:39,522
The foreign press
has been questioning Korea's status

1064
01:04:39,605 --> 01:04:41,482
-in human rights.
-It's going viral.

1065
01:04:41,565 --> 01:04:44,652
The comment section in the article
about our trial is blowing up.

1066
01:04:45,820 --> 01:04:49,198
Look at all these
"We seek asylum" hashtags.

1067
01:04:49,281 --> 01:04:51,826
Good. Things are going
according to plan.

1068
01:04:51,909 --> 01:04:54,286
The Ministry of Justice
must be going crazy right now.

1069
01:04:54,370 --> 01:04:57,289
They'll appeal but will try
to make a deal behind the scenes.

1070
01:04:57,373 --> 01:04:59,375
Let's get it over with quick!

1071
01:05:00,334 --> 01:05:01,460
Mr. Kang.

1072
01:05:02,169 --> 01:05:04,171
What is it, Mr. Hwang?
Why are you so serious?

1073
01:05:04,255 --> 01:05:08,592
I thought Kaya's Pikki Pikki dance
in working pants was so hilarious,

1074
01:05:08,676 --> 01:05:10,594
so I posted it on my social media page.

1075
01:05:11,512 --> 01:05:13,514
Gosh, you sure have unique taste.

1076
01:05:13,597 --> 01:05:14,432
So what about it?

1077
01:05:15,433 --> 01:05:16,684
But do you know

1078
01:05:16,767 --> 01:05:20,146
who shared it on her social media page?

1079
01:05:20,229 --> 01:05:21,147
What?

1080
01:05:21,897 --> 01:05:24,567
Gosh, you're so frustrating. Who did what?

1081
01:05:24,650 --> 01:05:26,152
-Uploaded it where?
-What's going on?

1082
01:05:28,279 --> 01:05:30,489
BLACK… PINK's Jennie?

1083
01:05:33,284 --> 01:05:35,369
Jennie from BLACKPINK?

1084
01:05:36,328 --> 01:05:37,830
What did he say?

1085
01:05:38,622 --> 01:05:39,457
Nan-hui!

1086
01:05:44,503 --> 01:05:45,838
Jennie.

1087
01:05:50,718 --> 01:05:52,094
Mr. Kang.

1088
01:05:52,178 --> 01:05:54,472
Please drop the refugee case.

1089
01:05:54,555 --> 01:05:56,432
It turned the Ministry of Justice
upside down.

1090
01:05:56,515 --> 01:05:59,351
What are you talking about?

1091
01:05:59,435 --> 01:06:01,479
You're the one who should drop it.

1092
01:06:01,562 --> 01:06:02,938
Drop the appeal.

1093
01:06:04,815 --> 01:06:07,443
Haven't you seen this yet?

1094
01:06:07,526 --> 01:06:11,030
Nationalistic YouTube creators
are going crazy right now.

1095
01:06:11,113 --> 01:06:15,117
You should be giving us a medal
for promoting Korea all over the world,

1096
01:06:15,201 --> 01:06:17,495
but instead, you're appealing
the first trial's ruling?

1097
01:06:17,578 --> 01:06:19,955
What kind of job are you doing?

1098
01:06:20,039 --> 01:06:23,709
If you drop the charge,
we will take care of Kaya's issue.

1099
01:06:27,505 --> 01:06:29,256
And how are you going to do that?

1100
01:06:29,340 --> 01:06:32,843
We'll issue a work visa so she can stay
in Korea without any issues

1101
01:06:32,927 --> 01:06:34,762
and give her financial support
to get settled.

1102
01:06:34,845 --> 01:06:37,264
If she wants, we can also find her a job--

1103
01:06:37,348 --> 01:06:38,182
She wants it.

1104
01:06:38,849 --> 01:06:42,812
Then, can I leave
assuming that you'll drop the suit?

1105
01:06:44,605 --> 01:06:45,606
You can go.

1106
01:06:49,110 --> 01:06:52,113
Now, shall we go
and fight the remaining battle?

1107
01:06:52,196 --> 01:06:54,949
The second hearing
for Kaya's father-in-law.

1108
01:06:55,032 --> 01:06:57,618
We have to send him back to jail
for a very long time.

1109
01:06:59,578 --> 01:07:01,664
You won't have to worry about it.

1110
01:07:02,373 --> 01:07:03,207
Why not?

1111
01:07:04,166 --> 01:07:05,918
He met the Grim Reaper.

1112
01:07:07,002 --> 01:07:09,004
-The Grim Reaper?
-Yes.

1113
01:07:10,548 --> 01:07:14,176
I lost my mind for a moment
and made a mistake while drunk.

1114
01:07:14,260 --> 01:07:15,886
I heard the criminals pray and say,

1115
01:07:15,970 --> 01:07:18,931
"Please let me avoid
Judge Jung the Grim Reaper."

1116
01:07:19,014 --> 01:07:21,976
They shouldn't have done the crimes then.
Those brazen bastards.

1117
01:07:22,059 --> 01:07:23,561
I'd like to say

1118
01:07:23,644 --> 01:07:28,274
that the 200 hours of community service
ordered in the first trial was excessive.

1119
01:07:28,774 --> 01:07:29,859
And lastly…

1120
01:07:29,942 --> 01:07:31,193
DIE

1121
01:07:31,277 --> 01:07:35,781
I expect a wise judgment by Your Honor
within a range permitted by law…

1122
01:07:39,118 --> 01:07:40,911
SENIOR ADVISOR OH GYU-JANG

1123
01:07:54,717 --> 01:07:55,885
Hello, my daughter.

1124
01:07:55,968 --> 01:07:57,970
-Did you ask for me, Father?
-Yes.

1125
01:07:58,554 --> 01:07:59,555
Take a seat.

1126
01:08:00,139 --> 01:08:00,973
Okay.

1127
01:08:04,435 --> 01:08:06,854
Did you see this too?

1128
01:08:10,024 --> 01:08:11,317
It's pretty fun.

1129
01:08:12,067 --> 01:08:14,361
Ever since Judge Kang came,
we've had no time to be bored.

1130
01:08:15,946 --> 01:08:17,072
Father,

1131
01:08:17,156 --> 01:08:21,285
you should step back from work now
and find a hobby to enjoy.

1132
01:08:21,368 --> 01:08:23,829
You can ride bikes,
just as you mentioned before.

1133
01:08:23,913 --> 01:08:26,040
You can play the electric guitar too.

1134
01:08:26,123 --> 01:08:26,999
Jung-in.

1135
01:08:28,792 --> 01:08:31,879
Having power is my hobby.

1136
01:08:35,758 --> 01:08:37,635
Riding bikes? Playing the guitar?

1137
01:08:38,219 --> 01:08:41,305
Those things are for petty citizens.

1138
01:08:42,181 --> 01:08:45,809
There's nothing in the world
more fun than power.

1139
01:08:46,685 --> 01:08:48,312
You should know as much

1140
01:08:48,395 --> 01:08:49,980
now that you're a CEO.

1141
01:08:51,815 --> 01:08:53,275
I'm doing my best

1142
01:08:54,902 --> 01:08:56,654
to not ruin your reputation.

1143
01:08:57,321 --> 01:09:00,032
Doing your best isn't enough.
You have to excel.

1144
01:09:03,827 --> 01:09:05,621
Disband Team Pro Bono.

1145
01:09:06,664 --> 01:09:07,498
What?

1146
01:09:09,625 --> 01:09:10,709
Father.

1147
01:09:17,299 --> 01:09:18,133
Hello.

1148
01:09:18,842 --> 01:09:20,511
-Hey.
-Hi.

1149
01:09:20,594 --> 01:09:22,554
-Hello.
-Hi.

1150
01:09:23,222 --> 01:09:25,599
It feels like I'm getting healthier.

1151
01:09:26,934 --> 01:09:28,477
AWON GENERAL HOSPITAL

1152
01:09:29,311 --> 01:09:31,855
The medical checkups from last time.

1153
01:09:33,148 --> 01:09:36,527
Mr. Kang. I'm a man with no fear.

1154
01:09:36,610 --> 01:09:41,323
But the only thing I'm afraid of
are syringe needles.

1155
01:09:41,407 --> 01:09:43,409
When they inserted the needle that day…

1156
01:09:43,492 --> 01:09:44,410
See?

1157
01:09:45,661 --> 01:09:47,162
My body doesn't respond

1158
01:09:47,663 --> 01:09:51,292
to anesthesia…

1159
01:09:52,668 --> 01:09:54,920
Hey, hold on tight.

1160
01:09:56,380 --> 01:09:57,381
Be careful.

1161
01:10:03,345 --> 01:10:04,930
-I got it!
-My goodness!

1162
01:10:05,014 --> 01:10:06,140
You scared me!

1163
01:10:06,223 --> 01:10:07,349
You got what?

1164
01:10:08,392 --> 01:10:09,226
You're innocent.

1165
01:10:10,227 --> 01:10:11,395
Of what?

1166
01:10:11,478 --> 01:10:13,731
You're innocent, Mr. Kang! Innocent!

1167
01:10:18,193 --> 01:10:19,486
What?

1168
01:10:48,140 --> 01:10:51,769
I was fired after getting blackmailed
with a video of me taking a bribe.

1169
01:10:51,852 --> 01:10:52,936
Then, I came here.

1170
01:10:53,020 --> 01:10:55,147
They're going to fire us all.
Starting with you.

1171
01:10:55,230 --> 01:10:58,525
Baekseung Law Firm has been
close behind Oh & Partners in revenue.

1172
01:10:58,609 --> 01:11:00,778
What if we can take away their clients?

1173
01:11:00,861 --> 01:11:03,280
We happen to have a meeting today,
so give it your best.

1174
01:11:04,156 --> 01:11:06,867
-What is she doing here?
-You got crushed in the first meeting?

1175
01:11:06,950 --> 01:11:09,328
-It wasn't that bad.
-It's at EK Entertainment this time.

1176
01:11:09,411 --> 01:11:11,121
You'll pitch against Baekseung.

1177
01:11:11,205 --> 01:11:13,582
We'll be protecting you, Elijah.

1178
01:11:13,665 --> 01:11:15,417
This video was uploaded.

1179
01:11:16,126 --> 01:11:17,086
What?

1180
01:11:17,169 --> 01:11:21,256
I guess not enough research
was done on the client's industry.

1181
01:11:27,513 --> 01:11:29,515
Subtitle translation by: Yoon Hyewon
